WEBVTT

00:00:29.259 --> 00:00:30.302
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

00:00:33.388 --> 00:00:35.014
CHARACTERS, EVENTS, ORGANIZATIONS,
AND PLACES IN THIS DRAMA ARE FICTITIOUS

00:00:35.015 --> 00:00:36.308
ALL CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
FILMED IN A SAFE ENVIRONMENT

00:00:37.934 --> 00:00:39.478
Then is it okay if I like you?

00:01:03.043 --> 00:01:04.251
Uh…

00:01:04.252 --> 00:01:07.464
I think we should turn this off.

00:01:09.049 --> 00:01:12.093
I didn't mean that…

00:01:12.094 --> 00:01:14.553
I didn't mean that, either.

00:01:14.554 --> 00:01:18.350
My grandmother kept talking
about us dating,

00:01:19.518 --> 00:01:20.811
so I was just…

00:01:21.645 --> 00:01:25.190
trying to stop that in advance
since you might feel uneasy.

00:01:25.774 --> 00:01:26.775
That's all.

00:01:27.359 --> 00:01:29.111
That's really it?

00:01:34.658 --> 00:01:36.076
Should there be something else?

00:01:39.830 --> 00:01:41.289
I'll start driving, then.

00:01:45.502 --> 00:01:46.585
EPISODE 5

00:01:46.586 --> 00:01:47.670
GYEONGJU

00:01:47.671 --> 00:01:50.965
The cold is expected
to arrive earlier this year than usual.

00:01:50.966 --> 00:01:54.760
The first snow may fall sooner
than average as well.

00:01:54.761 --> 00:01:56.763
The continental high-pressure system--

00:02:03.395 --> 00:02:05.439
It would be a shame to just leave.

00:02:06.940 --> 00:02:08.608
Can you pull over?

00:02:20.912 --> 00:02:24.416
Wow. It would've been a huge shame
if we'd just left.

00:02:29.296 --> 00:02:30.297
I hate snow.

00:02:31.506 --> 00:02:33.049
Especially the first snow.

00:02:34.509 --> 00:02:35.885
The first snow?

00:02:35.886 --> 00:02:37.888
Remember what I told you about my parents?

00:02:38.472 --> 00:02:42.309
The accident happened
on the first snowfall.

00:02:43.477 --> 00:02:46.438
So it became an unlucky day for me.

00:02:47.731 --> 00:02:49.064
Mmm.

00:02:49.065 --> 00:02:50.901
I know it's a lame jinx, though.

00:02:56.990 --> 00:03:01.036
Then I'll start hating
the first snow, too.

00:03:03.872 --> 00:03:05.122
Oh, um…

00:03:05.123 --> 00:03:07.667
I have a habit of copying other people.

00:03:12.714 --> 00:03:15.050
I'm not sure if it's okay to ask this,

00:03:16.593 --> 00:03:20.847
but when I talked about my mom's voice…

00:03:22.057 --> 00:03:24.518
you said there's someone you miss.

00:03:25.393 --> 00:03:26.686
That was your mother, right?

00:03:29.439 --> 00:03:31.149
Your grandmother told me.

00:03:32.859 --> 00:03:36.321
I was surprised when you spoke
like you experienced the same thing.

00:03:40.367 --> 00:03:42.869
Uh…

00:03:43.954 --> 00:03:45.037
Croissant.

00:03:45.038 --> 00:03:46.498
Croissant?

00:03:48.041 --> 00:03:49.251
The pastry?

00:03:50.460 --> 00:03:51.836
The crescent moon.

00:03:53.505 --> 00:03:55.048
It's "croissant" in French.

00:03:55.715 --> 00:03:59.636
Don't you crave croissants
when you see the crescent moon?

00:04:02.806 --> 00:04:04.723
Anyway, your grandmother said--

00:04:04.724 --> 00:04:06.059
What about the half-moon?

00:04:07.143 --> 00:04:08.936
Omurice!

00:04:08.937 --> 00:04:10.020
And the full moon?

00:04:10.021 --> 00:04:12.274
It's pizza. Huh?

00:04:13.483 --> 00:04:15.694
Was it just me, then?

00:04:17.153 --> 00:04:18.822
I'm craving pizza.

00:04:29.833 --> 00:04:32.210
Ben, we're here.

00:04:33.587 --> 00:04:35.797
Are they not here yet?

00:04:38.049 --> 00:04:40.175
Surprise!

00:04:43.638 --> 00:04:45.514
- How have you been?
- I'm good, I'm good.

00:04:45.515 --> 00:04:47.933
- It's great to see you here in Korea.
- Me too.

00:04:47.934 --> 00:04:49.685
Let me quickly introduce her.

00:04:49.686 --> 00:04:52.063
Guys, this is designer Haran Song.

00:04:52.647 --> 00:04:55.608
Uh… Nice to meet you.

00:04:55.609 --> 00:04:59.236
I'm Peter. Uh…

00:04:59.237 --> 00:05:01.614
- It's so great to meet you.
- Hi, nice to meet you.

00:05:01.615 --> 00:05:03.449
- This is my team.
- Nice to meet you. Hi.

00:05:03.450 --> 00:05:04.533
Nice to meet you.

00:05:04.534 --> 00:05:07.077
We're going to spend the morning
taking in the scenery,

00:05:07.078 --> 00:05:08.871
visiting some historic sites,

00:05:08.872 --> 00:05:11.624
and then we will head over
to Yangdong Village.

00:05:11.625 --> 00:05:16.629
So on page 3, there's more information
about Yangdong Village.

00:05:16.630 --> 00:05:21.550
So as you can see, there's a big tree.
This tree is more than 500 years old.

00:05:21.551 --> 00:05:23.886
It's really famous.

00:05:23.887 --> 00:05:26.764
So his father sent him to America,

00:05:26.765 --> 00:05:29.768
and he suffered there.

00:05:30.352 --> 00:05:31.936
"Something terrible"?

00:05:31.937 --> 00:05:34.272
What happened in the US?

00:05:34.856 --> 00:05:37.650
Why won't he tell me about himself?

00:05:37.651 --> 00:05:39.276
That's a great idea.
Let's use that tree.

00:05:39.277 --> 00:05:40.569
It's famous in Yangdong.

00:05:40.570 --> 00:05:43.781
Ms. Song,
about the materials you sent over…

00:05:43.782 --> 00:05:44.907
Yes.

00:05:44.908 --> 00:05:47.451
It's pretty decorative, right?

00:05:47.452 --> 00:05:48.827
We'll turn it into a pattern.

00:05:48.828 --> 00:05:52.373
Why am I someone you shouldn't like?

00:06:08.640 --> 00:06:10.641
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

00:06:12.560 --> 00:06:14.187
Oh?

00:06:16.106 --> 00:06:18.190
What are you doing?

00:06:18.191 --> 00:06:20.234
Oh. Playing a game to pick the driver.

00:06:20.235 --> 00:06:22.027
You saw our team, right?

00:06:22.028 --> 00:06:23.487
They're all mischievous.

00:06:24.572 --> 00:06:26.031
Did you lose?

00:06:26.032 --> 00:06:28.118
- Then I'll drive--
- I'm the king of games.

00:06:28.868 --> 00:06:30.912
I won, of course.

00:06:31.788 --> 00:06:33.038
We're here!

00:06:33.039 --> 00:06:34.331
Hey, Sol!

00:06:34.332 --> 00:06:35.791
Why are you alone?

00:06:35.792 --> 00:06:37.793
Raemee is here!

00:06:37.794 --> 00:06:41.130
Gosh, I just realized on the way here
how beautiful Gyeongju is.

00:06:41.131 --> 00:06:42.381
It's totally my style.

00:06:42.382 --> 00:06:46.218
It seems like
you're moving here.

00:06:46.219 --> 00:06:49.763
I need this much luggage
at least to dress for the occasion.

00:06:49.764 --> 00:06:52.349
Don't play dumb!

00:06:52.350 --> 00:06:54.769
- We're here, too.
- Me too.

00:06:55.687 --> 00:06:58.897
Okay, everybody's here.
We'll leave in 10 minutes. Okay, guys?

00:07:08.783 --> 00:07:10.159
Let's lie down!

00:07:13.163 --> 00:07:14.831
This is so nice.

00:07:35.518 --> 00:07:37.019
HWANGNIDAN STREET
GYEONGJU BREAD

00:08:35.703 --> 00:08:36.704
Yes, Ms. Kim.

00:08:37.163 --> 00:08:38.247
Seeing it in person,

00:08:38.248 --> 00:08:41.042
I think we should emphasize
the Korean elements a bit more.

00:08:42.460 --> 00:08:45.922
Then I'll come up with another sketch
with that in mind.

00:08:46.631 --> 00:08:47.841
All right.

00:08:50.718 --> 00:08:53.429
This is pretty tough.

00:08:56.850 --> 00:08:59.852
Aren't you tired?
It's a tough schedule, isn't it?

00:08:59.853 --> 00:09:01.354
It's okay.

00:09:02.689 --> 00:09:04.481
Everyone seems excited, though.

00:09:04.482 --> 00:09:07.109
You seem like friends
rather than colleagues.

00:09:07.110 --> 00:09:11.113
We weren't this close,
but after Too Much joined us…

00:09:12.532 --> 00:09:14.116
You didn't join at the same time?

00:09:14.117 --> 00:09:17.369
Too Much is several years my junior.
At school and at work.

00:09:17.370 --> 00:09:18.955
He joined this field pretty late.

00:09:19.914 --> 00:09:23.417
Oh. Then he studied something else
before animation?

00:09:23.418 --> 00:09:25.586
I don't know, either.

00:09:25.587 --> 00:09:30.383
He never tells me
what he did before entering CalArts.

00:09:31.301 --> 00:09:33.219
It's like he erased it.

00:09:34.596 --> 00:09:36.806
Erasing his time…

00:09:39.225 --> 00:09:40.642
Are you two badmouthing me?

00:09:40.643 --> 00:09:42.394
You caught us!

00:09:42.395 --> 00:09:43.897
I'm fleeing!

00:09:44.898 --> 00:09:46.398
You badmouthed me, didn't you?

00:09:46.399 --> 00:09:48.234
- No, we didn't.
- I think you did.

00:09:49.402 --> 00:09:50.986
Did you sketch something?

00:09:50.987 --> 00:09:53.114
- Oh… Yes. Do you want to see?
- Sure.

00:09:58.912 --> 00:09:59.995
Wow.

00:09:59.996 --> 00:10:02.540
Your grandmother said
you didn't draw for a while.

00:10:03.208 --> 00:10:05.584
How did you end up drawing again?

00:10:05.585 --> 00:10:06.835
I'm curious.

00:10:06.836 --> 00:10:08.338
Was there a special reason?

00:10:09.214 --> 00:10:10.965
Oh. Hmm…

00:10:15.303 --> 00:10:16.304
I'd like a ticket

00:10:16.971 --> 00:10:20.015
for the earliest departure anywhere
except the US.

00:10:20.016 --> 00:10:21.976
Hi, where are you from?

00:10:22.894 --> 00:10:25.897
Well, anyway… Enjoy Florence.

00:10:36.574 --> 00:10:39.410
THE PAST
THINGS TO DO FROM NOW ON

00:10:42.247 --> 00:10:44.874
THINGS I WANT TO DO FROM NOW ON

00:10:46.918 --> 00:10:49.837
DRAW

00:10:51.381 --> 00:10:52.839
I just…

00:10:54.842 --> 00:10:56.594
didn't want to live like a corpse.

00:10:57.845 --> 00:10:58.846
A corpse?

00:11:00.056 --> 00:11:02.976
Doesn't it feel like we time-traveled?

00:11:03.476 --> 00:11:06.478
This tree is over 500 years old.

00:11:06.479 --> 00:11:07.480
Mmm.

00:11:19.742 --> 00:11:23.203
If you can time travel,
when do you want to return to?

00:11:23.204 --> 00:11:25.122
Mmm… I don't want to go back.

00:11:26.332 --> 00:11:30.253
I don't have a past I want to return to.

00:11:31.713 --> 00:11:34.048
Doesn't everyone have
a certain moment, though?

00:11:35.675 --> 00:11:37.260
You never know when you'll die.

00:11:38.052 --> 00:11:41.596
You should enjoy your life
instead of regretting the past,

00:11:41.597 --> 00:11:42.974
so you won't feel upset later.

00:11:46.019 --> 00:11:47.311
Mmm.

00:11:47.312 --> 00:11:49.521
Maybe it's that free trial.

00:11:49.522 --> 00:11:51.357
I do feel kind of excited these days.

00:11:52.066 --> 00:11:55.194
We went to the Hangang River,
made pottery,

00:11:56.154 --> 00:11:57.280
and came here.

00:11:59.699 --> 00:12:01.700
You're doing great.

00:12:01.701 --> 00:12:05.830
Keep enjoying your life
like this every day,

00:12:06.789 --> 00:12:07.790
even when…

00:12:08.708 --> 00:12:09.917
I'm not here later.

00:12:36.569 --> 00:12:39.112
Oh? You changed your outfit.

00:12:39.113 --> 00:12:41.949
You weren't wearing that earlier.
Why did you change?

00:12:43.159 --> 00:12:46.578
Oh… I just bought it
while doing some trend research.

00:12:46.579 --> 00:12:50.248
That's strange.
It really isn't your style.

00:12:50.249 --> 00:12:52.417
It looks like
you picked it out in a hurry.

00:12:52.418 --> 00:12:54.336
Did I miss some kind of new trend?

00:12:54.337 --> 00:12:55.754
- Or--
- Shut up.

00:12:55.755 --> 00:12:57.672
You're so talkative.

00:12:58.841 --> 00:13:01.259
I'm just curious about you.

00:13:01.260 --> 00:13:03.596
This is my way
of expressing love and affection.

00:13:09.936 --> 00:13:12.355
I'll just go meet Cha Min.

00:13:21.447 --> 00:13:23.198
What's this awkward silence?

00:13:23.199 --> 00:13:25.617
Say something, Hayeong.

00:13:25.618 --> 00:13:28.745
You're usually talkative.
It'll seem like he's making you nervous.

00:13:28.746 --> 00:13:31.999
Just tease him or something,
like you usually do.

00:13:33.626 --> 00:13:36.128
- Is there something wrong?
- What?

00:13:36.129 --> 00:13:38.380
You seem quieter than usual.

00:13:38.381 --> 00:13:39.756
Do you think

00:13:39.757 --> 00:13:44.261
I'm always…
just chatting loudly?

00:13:44.262 --> 00:13:45.680
That's not what I meant.

00:13:46.556 --> 00:13:47.557
Sorry.

00:13:48.850 --> 00:13:51.268
But aren't you getting off?

00:13:51.269 --> 00:13:53.061
Right. I am.

00:13:55.606 --> 00:13:56.858
Be careful.

00:14:32.435 --> 00:14:33.560
Hey, Manjae.

00:14:33.561 --> 00:14:35.520
Did you move or something?

00:14:35.521 --> 00:14:38.899
You said you'd drop by sometime,
but you never came.

00:14:38.900 --> 00:14:42.235
Sorry, I've been pretty busy.

00:14:42.236 --> 00:14:44.696
Why don't I drop by after work today?

00:14:44.697 --> 00:14:46.574
Sure. Come and see Genius, too.

00:14:50.036 --> 00:14:51.412
Okay. I'll see you later.

00:15:15.102 --> 00:15:16.938
Hey, it's Yougyum.

00:15:17.438 --> 00:15:18.481
What?

00:15:18.981 --> 00:15:21.066
He just came out of a jewelry shop.

00:15:21.067 --> 00:15:23.319
I bet he bought matching rings.

00:15:23.986 --> 00:15:25.071
You're so lucky, Hadam.

00:15:31.160 --> 00:15:32.827
Matching rings?

00:15:37.959 --> 00:15:40.752
Thank you for the food!

00:15:47.885 --> 00:15:49.553
Try this one, try this one.

00:15:53.224 --> 00:15:55.601
Yummy. This is amazing.

00:15:57.687 --> 00:15:58.853
I'll eat those for you.

00:15:58.854 --> 00:16:01.190
The snot and neon aliens.

00:16:01.983 --> 00:16:02.984
Thanks.

00:16:04.235 --> 00:16:07.362
Don't you guys think that
Yangdong Village was just so gorgeous?

00:16:07.363 --> 00:16:09.656
It was really unique, don't you think?

00:16:09.657 --> 00:16:12.158
I totally agree.
It kind of felt like it was timeless.

00:16:12.159 --> 00:16:15.328
Actually, I think it feels
even better than the photo. Right?

00:16:15.329 --> 00:16:17.163
Yeah, it's so beautiful.

00:16:17.164 --> 00:16:20.501
But do you know the scene
where Won first goes back to the past?

00:16:22.336 --> 00:16:27.590
Uh… Maybe we can make that moment
a little bit deeper. Do you guys agree?

00:16:27.591 --> 00:16:30.427
Maybe that's exactly
what we should do, yeah.

00:16:30.428 --> 00:16:31.511
Awesome.

00:16:31.512 --> 00:16:33.471
- Okay, then… Mmm.
- Let's do it.

00:16:33.472 --> 00:16:35.682
Thank you so much. Let's just eat first.

00:16:35.683 --> 00:16:37.559
All together. One, two, three!

00:16:37.560 --> 00:16:40.395
The ocean!

00:16:50.197 --> 00:16:52.407
Wait!

00:16:52.408 --> 00:16:54.285
No, wait! Hey, Raemee!

00:17:33.074 --> 00:17:35.201
I can't even decide on a concept.

00:17:36.827 --> 00:17:38.621
You there, who's mulling over pens.

00:17:39.497 --> 00:17:42.666
Do you want to go see the sea cave
to clear your head?

00:17:43.793 --> 00:17:45.335
Nice timing.

00:17:45.336 --> 00:17:47.337
I needed
a reason to take a break.

00:17:51.884 --> 00:17:52.927
Oh, right.

00:17:55.221 --> 00:17:56.972
I never told you that, though.

00:17:58.516 --> 00:18:00.392
I told you I don't eat oysters,

00:18:00.393 --> 00:18:03.396
but I never told you
eggplants seemed like neon aliens.

00:18:04.855 --> 00:18:06.022
I'll eat those for you.

00:18:06.023 --> 00:18:08.066
The snot and neon aliens.

00:18:08.067 --> 00:18:09.901
It's neon-colored. Yuck!

00:18:09.902 --> 00:18:12.237
The taste of a neon alien.

00:18:14.949 --> 00:18:15.950
Uh…

00:18:20.121 --> 00:18:22.455
No, how else would you know?

00:18:22.456 --> 00:18:23.499
I guess I told you.

00:18:24.208 --> 00:18:25.792
Sorry, I must've forgotten.

00:18:25.793 --> 00:18:26.876
Is it this way?

00:18:42.643 --> 00:18:43.644
What are you doing?

00:18:48.858 --> 00:18:51.902
Don't you want to ride a plane
when you see a vapor trail?

00:18:53.738 --> 00:18:55.740
I actually rode one after seeing one.

00:18:57.032 --> 00:19:00.369
I went to meet the person
who gave me that fountain pen I lost.

00:19:02.204 --> 00:19:04.165
I used to work at a different company,

00:19:04.790 --> 00:19:09.336
and he was the brother of my team leader
who really cared for me.

00:19:10.337 --> 00:19:14.007
But soon after we started dating,
he went to Boston to study.

00:19:17.178 --> 00:19:18.428
Nice to meet you.

00:19:18.429 --> 00:19:20.638
I'm Kang Hyeokchan.

00:19:20.639 --> 00:19:22.056
I'm glad you're Korean, too.

00:19:22.057 --> 00:19:23.225
I hope we get along.

00:19:27.146 --> 00:19:28.355
Are you okay?

00:19:33.819 --> 00:19:36.155
Are you all right? You've gone pale.

00:19:38.699 --> 00:19:40.951
If I'm not okay, will you carry me?

00:19:41.660 --> 00:19:43.661
Are you seriously joking right now?

00:19:43.662 --> 00:19:45.247
Are you sure you're okay?

00:19:46.624 --> 00:19:48.417
I'll be okay.

00:19:49.668 --> 00:19:51.461
It's all going to be okay.

00:20:01.764 --> 00:20:04.016
- Yougyum!
- Hey, Hadam.

00:20:06.477 --> 00:20:09.854
My academy ends at 9:00 p.m.
Should we meet after?

00:20:09.855 --> 00:20:11.231
What?

00:20:11.232 --> 00:20:13.150
Did we plan to meet today?

00:20:13.734 --> 00:20:14.984
Mmm…

00:20:14.985 --> 00:20:19.239
No, but I think you have a reason
to meet me later.

00:20:19.240 --> 00:20:20.366
I don't.

00:20:21.033 --> 00:20:24.035
Why don't you spend some time
with your grandma--

00:20:24.036 --> 00:20:26.704
Why are you suddenly
bringing up my grandma?

00:20:26.705 --> 00:20:27.914
What?

00:20:29.333 --> 00:20:31.501
Oh… Well…

00:20:31.502 --> 00:20:33.044
Hey, Changmo!

00:20:33.045 --> 00:20:36.214
I have something urgent
to discuss with Changmo, so I have to go.

00:20:36.215 --> 00:20:37.675
Hey, Changmo!

00:20:39.510 --> 00:20:43.013
What? Changmo isn't even there.

00:20:43.889 --> 00:20:46.392
He should hurry up
and give me the ring.

00:20:47.768 --> 00:20:51.521
Unfortunately, it seems like
he gave the ring to Han Sora.

00:20:52.606 --> 00:20:54.732
She didn't have that a few days ago.

00:20:54.733 --> 00:20:56.235
But she was wearing this
in her recent feed.

00:20:57.403 --> 00:20:59.363
Don't be ridiculous.

00:21:00.155 --> 00:21:02.991
If a girl group trainee with her looks
hits on him,

00:21:02.992 --> 00:21:04.827
he could easily fall for her.

00:21:14.587 --> 00:21:16.672
That's nonsense.

00:21:19.592 --> 00:21:20.675
GUARDIAN

00:21:25.514 --> 00:21:27.390
I wanted to give you this.

00:21:27.391 --> 00:21:31.728
It finally found its owner
after over 50 years.

00:21:36.150 --> 00:21:38.360
What? "La Vie en rose"?

00:21:39.278 --> 00:21:41.738
This is my favorite song.

00:21:41.739 --> 00:21:44.365
But what did you mean
by this finding its owner?

00:21:44.366 --> 00:21:48.077
You were humming that song all the time
when we lived in Chuncheon.

00:21:48.078 --> 00:21:50.914
I played it with the harmonica, too.

00:21:50.915 --> 00:21:51.999
Right.

00:21:52.583 --> 00:21:53.666
I remember.

00:21:53.667 --> 00:21:55.418
After I went to college in Seoul

00:21:55.419 --> 00:21:58.838
and heard you got accepted
to a medical school the next year,

00:21:58.839 --> 00:22:01.758
I went to Chuncheon to give you this.

00:22:01.759 --> 00:22:04.510
I waited by the tree
where we always hung out,

00:22:04.511 --> 00:22:07.430
but you never showed.

00:22:07.431 --> 00:22:08.598
You waited for me?

00:22:08.599 --> 00:22:12.852
It snowed like crazy that day.

00:22:12.853 --> 00:22:15.772
I almost became a snowman
waiting for you there.

00:22:16.857 --> 00:22:20.610
I only heard the news later on.

00:22:20.611 --> 00:22:23.905
The news that I ran off with my tuition
and hopped on a flight to Paris?

00:22:23.906 --> 00:22:25.823
Yes!

00:22:25.824 --> 00:22:29.827
I didn't get to give you this record,
so I just listened to it.

00:22:29.828 --> 00:22:32.372
It was so nice.

00:22:32.373 --> 00:22:35.417
That's how I got obsessed
and started collecting vinyls.

00:22:36.293 --> 00:22:38.252
And this is the result.

00:22:38.253 --> 00:22:42.006
It's all your fault, Kim Nabong.

00:22:44.927 --> 00:22:46.178
Is that so?

00:22:50.057 --> 00:22:53.310
We were dazzling back then.

00:22:57.064 --> 00:22:58.315
It's nice seeing you again.

00:22:59.483 --> 00:23:02.569
I'd been so busy pushing forward
that I'd forgotten about our old hometown.

00:23:03.779 --> 00:23:05.196
I agree.

00:23:06.365 --> 00:23:08.491
Instead of just reminiscing,

00:23:08.492 --> 00:23:11.202
why don't we visit Chuncheon sometime?

00:23:11.203 --> 00:23:12.286
Chuncheon?

00:23:12.287 --> 00:23:15.040
Aren't you curious
whether that tree is still there

00:23:15.541 --> 00:23:18.418
and how much our neighborhood has changed?

00:23:19.753 --> 00:23:21.088
Right.

00:23:21.880 --> 00:23:23.673
All right, let's go there sometime.

00:23:23.674 --> 00:23:25.384
Okay. Let's do that.

00:23:42.067 --> 00:23:44.987
Lab, glass tube, blood…

00:23:45.696 --> 00:23:46.780
Whose blood?

00:23:49.241 --> 00:23:50.576
Yes, Ms. Kim.

00:23:51.368 --> 00:23:53.579
Je Raemee sent his design?

00:23:55.247 --> 00:23:57.374
Oh. Sorry, I haven't
sketched anything yet.

00:23:59.460 --> 00:24:01.961
If you don't want to suffer again
because of your past,

00:24:01.962 --> 00:24:04.298
it would be best
to keep a distance from her.

00:24:05.382 --> 00:24:06.884
Did something else happen

00:24:07.801 --> 00:24:09.511
besides the explosion?

00:24:11.055 --> 00:24:13.222
Hurry up. Why are you so slow?

00:24:13.223 --> 00:24:14.724
Sorry.

00:24:14.725 --> 00:24:17.393
All right, everybody.
Let's head back and get some rest.

00:24:17.394 --> 00:24:18.686
Yeah, let's go.

00:24:18.687 --> 00:24:20.772
We'll see you later.

00:24:23.067 --> 00:24:24.860
Oh? Where's Ms. Song?

00:24:25.694 --> 00:24:28.781
- Huh?
- What? Weren't you with her?

00:24:29.531 --> 00:24:31.282
You were hanging out the whole time.

00:24:31.283 --> 00:24:34.494
She said she forgot her scarf.
She went to get it.

00:24:34.495 --> 00:24:36.829
Goodness. She's a klutz sometimes.

00:24:44.630 --> 00:24:45.631
Oh, uh…

00:24:46.090 --> 00:24:47.882
I'll go and get her. You go ahead.

00:24:55.641 --> 00:24:56.809
Ms. Song!

00:24:57.851 --> 00:24:58.977
Ms. Song!

00:25:01.105 --> 00:25:02.814
Song Haran!

00:25:05.734 --> 00:25:06.859
Oh?

00:25:06.860 --> 00:25:07.944
Why were you--

00:25:07.945 --> 00:25:09.278
Why are you so fast?

00:25:09.279 --> 00:25:11.490
I…

00:25:12.074 --> 00:25:13.908
I thought I'd left this here,

00:25:13.909 --> 00:25:15.952
but I found it in my pocket
and headed down.

00:25:15.953 --> 00:25:17.703
But then I heard you went to find me.

00:25:17.704 --> 00:25:20.331
I kept calling, but you wouldn't answer.

00:25:20.332 --> 00:25:22.084
I'm sorry.

00:25:22.501 --> 00:25:24.252
I guess I didn't hear it over the rain.

00:25:24.253 --> 00:25:26.254
I should've been more careful.

00:25:26.255 --> 00:25:27.839
You're always apologizing.

00:25:27.840 --> 00:25:29.465
- Let's go.
- Okay.

00:25:35.639 --> 00:25:37.431
Let's get out of the rain.

00:25:37.432 --> 00:25:39.059
Over there.

00:25:44.189 --> 00:25:45.607
Sit down.

00:25:46.400 --> 00:25:48.610
Oh. Thanks.

00:25:50.195 --> 00:25:51.821
Are you hurt?

00:25:51.822 --> 00:25:53.489
No, it's nothing.

00:25:56.076 --> 00:25:58.704
You shouldn't climb
with your shoelaces so loose.

00:26:00.455 --> 00:26:01.914
Your feet must have hurt a lot.

00:26:01.915 --> 00:26:03.667
Hey, it's dirty.

00:26:04.668 --> 00:26:06.461
Tell me if it keeps hurting.

00:26:07.087 --> 00:26:08.797
I'll carry you if I have to.

00:26:15.012 --> 00:26:16.971
I can't hear on this side.

00:26:18.056 --> 00:26:20.892
So his father sent him to America,

00:26:20.893 --> 00:26:24.062
and he suffered there.

00:26:27.399 --> 00:26:28.901
To be honest, I'm curious.

00:26:29.651 --> 00:26:30.944
About what?

00:26:31.528 --> 00:26:34.072
About what I heard from your grandmother.

00:26:35.199 --> 00:26:38.118
I want to know what happened in America,

00:26:39.494 --> 00:26:42.788
what you meant by being trapped in winter,

00:26:42.789 --> 00:26:45.209
and who freed you from it.

00:26:45.834 --> 00:26:48.754
I'm getting more comfortable around you,

00:26:49.421 --> 00:26:52.048
and I've been telling you
things about myself,

00:26:52.049 --> 00:26:53.383
but…

00:26:54.218 --> 00:26:56.720
you don't seem to be telling me
much about yourself.

00:27:04.561 --> 00:27:06.980
I started studying animation
six years ago.

00:27:07.689 --> 00:27:10.483
I worked my butt off and graduated early

00:27:10.484 --> 00:27:13.527
then entered my current company
as a character designer.

00:27:13.528 --> 00:27:16.030
I became a supervisor by luck

00:27:16.031 --> 00:27:18.575
since Won was a Korean character.

00:27:20.327 --> 00:27:23.538
I commute by bike

00:27:24.247 --> 00:27:27.249
since the office
is a 10-minute ride from home.

00:27:27.250 --> 00:27:29.460
You met my teammates, right?

00:27:29.461 --> 00:27:30.587
Everyone's really close.

00:27:31.296 --> 00:27:32.464
- And--
- Wait.

00:27:34.299 --> 00:27:36.468
- What are you talking about?
- I'm sorry,

00:27:38.220 --> 00:27:39.888
but I'll use it now.

00:27:42.265 --> 00:27:44.892
You said it's okay
to keep some secrets to yourself.

00:27:44.893 --> 00:27:47.061
You tell me a secret too next time.

00:27:47.062 --> 00:27:49.063
We can keep big secrets to ourselves.

00:27:49.064 --> 00:27:51.065
Just a small one.

00:27:51.066 --> 00:27:54.528
I'll tell you everything
about the present…

00:27:57.489 --> 00:27:58.824
but I'll use that card…

00:28:00.742 --> 00:28:01.994
for my past.

00:28:03.495 --> 00:28:04.496
Sorry.

00:28:06.957 --> 00:28:07.958
Ah…

00:28:08.875 --> 00:28:09.959
Oh, no.

00:28:09.960 --> 00:28:12.045
I guess I was being really rude.

00:28:12.671 --> 00:28:15.798
Right, we agreed
to do a three-month trial,

00:28:15.799 --> 00:28:17.592
but I was prying too much.

00:28:18.635 --> 00:28:21.346
I was being selfish.
I'm so sorry.

00:28:33.483 --> 00:28:35.986
This looks so delicious.

00:28:39.823 --> 00:28:41.949
- Thank you.
- Yeah, no problem.

00:28:41.950 --> 00:28:45.327
The staff prepared this since
the costume team is leaving tomorrow.

00:28:45.328 --> 00:28:47.621
- Thank you.
- That's so nice.

00:28:47.622 --> 00:28:48.914
I'm so touched.

00:28:48.915 --> 00:28:51.042
Do we seriously have to leave this behind

00:28:51.043 --> 00:28:53.085
and return to Seoul?

00:28:53.086 --> 00:28:55.379
I can't leave!

00:28:55.380 --> 00:28:58.174
Since this is our last night,

00:28:58.175 --> 00:29:00.176
let us all have a drink.

00:29:02.679 --> 00:29:04.221
Everyone… Cheers!

00:29:04.222 --> 00:29:07.266
Cheers!

00:29:07.267 --> 00:29:09.727
♪ Altogether
Game start ♪

00:29:09.728 --> 00:29:11.103
- Numbers game! One!
- Two!

00:29:11.104 --> 00:29:12.188
Three!

00:29:13.523 --> 00:29:15.816
Drink!

00:29:15.817 --> 00:29:17.026
♪ Drink up ♪

00:29:17.027 --> 00:29:18.652
It's my first time seeing her drink.

00:29:18.653 --> 00:29:20.738
Wait, stop. I have to film this.

00:29:20.739 --> 00:29:22.615
Can you drink like a beer model?

00:29:22.616 --> 00:29:24.366
No…

00:29:24.367 --> 00:29:26.286
Why are you so pretty?

00:29:29.164 --> 00:29:31.457
♪ Altogether
Game start ♪

00:29:31.458 --> 00:29:32.666
♪ Three, six, nine ♪

00:29:32.667 --> 00:29:33.876
♪ Three, six, nine ♪

00:29:40.383 --> 00:29:42.844
Why are you suddenly so serious?
It doesn't suit you.

00:29:43.345 --> 00:29:44.971
Ben.

00:29:45.472 --> 00:29:46.848
Hiding something

00:29:47.682 --> 00:29:49.392
and not telling the truth

00:29:50.727 --> 00:29:52.687
is the same as lying, right?

00:29:53.271 --> 00:29:54.272
That's so random.

00:29:55.440 --> 00:29:56.607
Hide what, though?

00:29:56.608 --> 00:30:01.529
You mean like how Aladdin
hid the fact that he was a petty thief?

00:30:03.365 --> 00:30:04.950
I guess it's similar.

00:30:06.493 --> 00:30:07.827
It's just…

00:30:07.828 --> 00:30:10.664
The other person is being honest with me,

00:30:12.332 --> 00:30:13.875
but if I keep…

00:30:15.502 --> 00:30:16.753
hiding things

00:30:17.587 --> 00:30:19.464
and never being honest,

00:30:20.590 --> 00:30:22.384
what will happen in the end?

00:30:24.928 --> 00:30:25.929
Ah.

00:30:27.347 --> 00:30:28.390
Do you remember?

00:30:29.099 --> 00:30:32.144
What the genie says
to Aladdin when he says

00:30:33.228 --> 00:30:35.147
he wants to keep pretending
to be a prince?

00:30:36.314 --> 00:30:37.315
Mmm.

00:30:38.692 --> 00:30:42.863
The more you gain
with deception,

00:30:45.198 --> 00:30:48.451
the less you can truly gain.

00:30:48.869 --> 00:30:49.953
That's right.

00:30:51.121 --> 00:30:53.622
It may seem like
you're gaining something now,

00:30:53.623 --> 00:30:56.459
but you'll probably end up
paying the price for it.

00:30:57.919 --> 00:30:59.211
Paying the price…

00:31:21.610 --> 00:31:23.069
What are you doing here alone?

00:31:25.614 --> 00:31:27.574
I'm trying to sober up
so I can drink more.

00:31:28.241 --> 00:31:29.951
It's been a while since I drank.

00:31:30.660 --> 00:31:32.078
You're a heavy drinker.

00:31:32.704 --> 00:31:34.122
How's your foot?

00:31:34.706 --> 00:31:36.958
You hurt yourself
because of Grandma's scarf.

00:31:37.876 --> 00:31:38.919
I'm okay.

00:31:45.258 --> 00:31:46.259
Look, aren't they pretty?

00:31:50.931 --> 00:31:54.308
Maybe it's because I lost
the pen I used for seven years,

00:31:54.309 --> 00:31:56.853
but I couldn't sketch anything
during the two days here.

00:31:58.063 --> 00:32:00.689
Maybe it's because
I couldn't stop thinking about it.

00:32:00.690 --> 00:32:02.525
I've been so distracted lately.

00:32:03.944 --> 00:32:09.157
Until now, I thought that pen was special
because of the person who gifted it to me.

00:32:10.700 --> 00:32:12.535
But I'm not so sure now.

00:32:13.078 --> 00:32:15.746
Maybe I just feel strange

00:32:15.747 --> 00:32:18.749
because I lost something
my hand had gotten used to

00:32:18.750 --> 00:32:21.127
after all those years.

00:32:23.797 --> 00:32:26.716
The person who gave me that pen died.

00:32:28.468 --> 00:32:31.054
I guess that's why
I was so attached to it.

00:32:32.097 --> 00:32:34.014
Not long ago,

00:32:34.015 --> 00:32:38.102
I would have done anything I could
to avoid coming here.

00:32:38.103 --> 00:32:39.604
But this time,

00:32:40.105 --> 00:32:43.108
I had quite a lot of fun.

00:32:43.650 --> 00:32:45.109
Like I was on a spring picnic.

00:32:46.987 --> 00:32:48.863
I guess we have grown quite close,

00:32:49.531 --> 00:32:52.826
seeing how I'm telling you
things I'm not okay with.

00:32:53.994 --> 00:32:57.914
You know we're not real friends
if we're always pretending to be okay.

00:33:02.627 --> 00:33:05.297
Thank you for asking to be friends

00:33:06.756 --> 00:33:08.258
and for knocking on my door.

00:33:09.217 --> 00:33:10.719
You made me stop hiding,

00:33:11.761 --> 00:33:15.974
and you made me
able to tell you sad things, too.

00:33:18.101 --> 00:33:20.811
Stop thanking me. I didn't do anything.

00:33:20.812 --> 00:33:22.313
Thank you.

00:33:22.314 --> 00:33:24.983
I just feel like
pouring my heart out today.

00:33:26.568 --> 00:33:28.278
I really am grateful.

00:33:36.578 --> 00:33:39.331
Can I borrow that for a moment?

00:33:40.665 --> 00:33:41.958
- This?
- Yes.

00:33:50.383 --> 00:33:51.384
Odd or even?

00:33:51.843 --> 00:33:53.427
That's so random.

00:33:53.428 --> 00:33:55.513
Is there a prize if I guess right?

00:33:57.223 --> 00:33:58.224
If you guess right,

00:34:00.268 --> 00:34:02.270
I'll tell you everything.

00:34:03.229 --> 00:34:04.397
I feel like

00:34:05.857 --> 00:34:07.817
telling you everything today, too.

00:34:09.027 --> 00:34:11.445
- Tell me what?
- I think I should stop

00:34:11.446 --> 00:34:12.697
hiding things about myself.

00:34:13.990 --> 00:34:15.157
Oh…

00:34:15.158 --> 00:34:17.910
If it's because of what I said,
you don't have to--

00:34:17.911 --> 00:34:19.161
Odd or even?

00:34:33.468 --> 00:34:34.469
Odd.

00:34:45.772 --> 00:34:46.980
Odd.

00:34:54.989 --> 00:34:57.199
Who keeps messaging?

00:34:57.200 --> 00:34:58.618
It's me.

00:34:59.202 --> 00:35:01.203
I'm uploading our photos
to our group chat.

00:35:01.204 --> 00:35:02.622
Oh…

00:35:06.042 --> 00:35:08.670
- Mmm.
- Hi, Hayeong. Did you see…

00:35:11.089 --> 00:35:12.090
What?

00:35:13.216 --> 00:35:14.718
I'm not sure…

00:35:16.845 --> 00:35:18.930
if I have the right to tell you

00:35:20.682 --> 00:35:22.016
about myself.

00:35:23.226 --> 00:35:24.436
To be honest…

00:35:28.648 --> 00:35:29.649
I'm scared.

00:35:30.984 --> 00:35:34.279
You asked me what happened in America.

00:35:35.947 --> 00:35:37.073
I…

00:35:39.993 --> 00:35:41.119
was actually…

00:35:45.665 --> 00:35:47.709
in Boston, attending…

00:35:51.463 --> 00:35:53.005
Haran's a total lightweight.

00:35:53.006 --> 00:35:54.465
She can't drink a single drop.

00:35:54.466 --> 00:35:55.924
Don't let her drink anything.

00:35:55.925 --> 00:35:58.719
- Stop!
- She can't drink at all!

00:35:58.720 --> 00:36:00.638
- Wait!
- Ms. Song!

00:36:46.726 --> 00:36:48.394
Hey. Sorry, Haran.

00:36:49.103 --> 00:36:50.354
That song?

00:36:50.355 --> 00:36:52.397
Okay, I'll listen to it.

00:36:52.398 --> 00:36:54.608
Can you message her back?

00:36:54.609 --> 00:36:56.109
Sorry. Do me a solid.

00:36:56.110 --> 00:36:58.237
Anything that a woman
in her twenties can use.

00:36:58.238 --> 00:37:01.491
I have to go to the hospital
because of my hand.

00:37:25.640 --> 00:37:26.849
Sorry.

00:37:26.850 --> 00:37:30.102
- Thanks, Chan.
- Who's that? Your friend?

00:37:30.103 --> 00:37:31.729
No, just my roommate.

00:37:34.107 --> 00:37:36.567
Sorry, Ran. My professor's calling.

00:37:36.568 --> 00:37:37.819
I'll call you back later.

00:37:39.362 --> 00:37:40.405
Sujin. You're here?

00:37:40.905 --> 00:37:41.906
I'll head out now.

00:37:44.492 --> 00:37:45.617
I'll be away for a few weeks.

00:37:45.618 --> 00:37:48.413
I'm traveling around the East Coast
during vacation.

00:37:49.205 --> 00:37:53.001
If our professor asks for me,
say I'm taking a break because of my hand.

00:38:18.860 --> 00:38:22.446
Getting close to someone
is really difficult…

00:38:22.447 --> 00:38:24.282
No, it's scary for me.

00:38:36.711 --> 00:38:39.004
It's all thanks to this pen.

00:38:39.005 --> 00:38:41.131
It's really valuable to me,
so I have to find it.

00:38:42.634 --> 00:38:44.551
Chan, I saw a vapor trail earlier.

00:38:44.552 --> 00:38:47.388
But that made me want
to get on a plane to go see you.

00:38:49.015 --> 00:38:51.225
Whether you're a guy or not,
I don't want to get close.

00:39:41.985 --> 00:39:44.112
It's morning?

00:39:56.708 --> 00:39:59.084
Hey. You spoke as if you were
a heavy drinker,

00:39:59.085 --> 00:40:03.548
but you passed out right away.

00:40:04.465 --> 00:40:09.011
I don't usually pass out
after drinking like that,

00:40:09.012 --> 00:40:11.638
but the alcohol tasted really good.

00:40:11.639 --> 00:40:15.393
Maybe it was because the weather
was so nice.

00:40:19.397 --> 00:40:20.564
Hey, Sujin.

00:40:24.277 --> 00:40:26.486
It's okay to be a lightweight.

00:40:26.487 --> 00:40:28.238
Why are you looking at me with pity?

00:40:28.239 --> 00:40:30.574
No, I'm not looking at you that way.

00:40:30.575 --> 00:40:33.786
You are. You just looked at me
like I was a lost puppy.

00:40:37.290 --> 00:40:38.291
Hmm.

00:40:42.128 --> 00:40:45.047
It's pitiful that
you're waiting for your old owner.

00:40:45.048 --> 00:40:47.884
I should be good to you
so you won't remember them.

00:40:49.427 --> 00:40:51.095
Is that how I looked at you?

00:40:52.305 --> 00:40:53.765
No need to say it like that…

00:40:54.390 --> 00:40:56.433
Let's go. Oh.

00:40:56.434 --> 00:40:58.603
- Bring your jacket.
- Where are we going?

00:40:59.187 --> 00:41:00.979
A hangover cure walk?

00:41:00.980 --> 00:41:03.941
If walking cured hangovers,
hangover soup places would close down.

00:41:05.485 --> 00:41:08.988
But when exactly did I pass out?

00:41:10.073 --> 00:41:11.240
Don't you remember?

00:41:12.617 --> 00:41:13.785
This.

00:41:17.413 --> 00:41:19.123
Right. Odd or even.

00:41:19.707 --> 00:41:23.294
I should have said odd.
Why did I guess even?

00:41:24.128 --> 00:41:26.672
- You didn't…
- Let's just say I did.

00:41:27.924 --> 00:41:30.842
There's no need to know everything.

00:41:30.843 --> 00:41:31.927
Still…

00:41:31.928 --> 00:41:34.721
You used your card
so you wouldn't have to tell me.

00:41:34.722 --> 00:41:36.557
It must have been something bad.

00:41:37.225 --> 00:41:39.435
I don't want to force you
to talk about it.

00:41:40.436 --> 00:41:43.856
There's no need to dig into your scars
to learn more about you.

00:41:47.902 --> 00:41:50.029
And even if I don't know about it,

00:41:50.947 --> 00:41:52.949
we're already quite close, right?

00:41:58.955 --> 00:42:01.373
Oh, right.

00:42:01.374 --> 00:42:02.707
Here.

00:42:02.708 --> 00:42:03.917
Honey water.

00:42:06.045 --> 00:42:09.548
Hangover medicine, hangover drink,

00:42:09.549 --> 00:42:12.426
roasted eggs, and…

00:42:13.094 --> 00:42:14.971
They must have been really kind to you.

00:42:15.513 --> 00:42:16.596
Who?

00:42:16.597 --> 00:42:19.684
The person who showed you
a way to keep going.

00:42:20.601 --> 00:42:22.103
The one who kept reaching out.

00:42:23.229 --> 00:42:26.231
I just wondered
if you're so sweet to other people

00:42:26.232 --> 00:42:28.693
because you learned it from them.

00:42:34.490 --> 00:42:36.450
How should I say it…

00:42:37.076 --> 00:42:38.327
I'm no match.

00:42:39.245 --> 00:42:41.538
This is nothing
compared to what I received.

00:42:41.539 --> 00:42:43.749
I received something so incredible

00:42:44.667 --> 00:42:46.127
that I could never repay her.

00:42:48.296 --> 00:42:49.671
Was it your girlfriend?

00:42:49.672 --> 00:42:52.675
No, of course not. I wouldn't dare.

00:42:54.051 --> 00:42:56.262
It wasn't like that. Mmm…

00:42:57.096 --> 00:42:58.097
She was just…

00:42:59.640 --> 00:43:02.643
someone who broadened my world.

00:43:03.311 --> 00:43:05.312
Broadened your world?

00:43:05.313 --> 00:43:06.314
Yes.

00:43:07.899 --> 00:43:09.775
She let me experience things

00:43:11.110 --> 00:43:12.862
that I couldn't see or feel before.

00:43:14.238 --> 00:43:18.201
My world used to be
black and white, but she…

00:43:20.203 --> 00:43:22.079
filled it with vibrant colors.

00:43:26.459 --> 00:43:28.252
Right. High five!

00:43:28.878 --> 00:43:31.088
I have a habit of doing high fives
when I'm grateful.

00:43:31.672 --> 00:43:33.507
You're grateful? All of a sudden?

00:43:34.634 --> 00:43:35.843
I found the answer.

00:43:36.969 --> 00:43:39.847
My choice was filled with question marks,

00:43:40.389 --> 00:43:44.268
but you just changed them
to exclamation marks.

00:43:45.811 --> 00:43:46.895
Your choice?

00:43:46.896 --> 00:43:48.605
I chose never to do anything

00:43:48.606 --> 00:43:52.485
that might get in the way
of her happiness.

00:43:53.402 --> 00:43:55.821
Thanks to you, I just realized

00:43:56.447 --> 00:43:59.992
that not digging up old wounds
is also a way…

00:44:01.452 --> 00:44:03.829
of protecting their happiness.

00:44:04.997 --> 00:44:06.540
That's why I'm asking

00:44:07.291 --> 00:44:08.292
for a high five.

00:44:09.168 --> 00:44:12.212
Well, I have no idea
what you're talking about,

00:44:12.213 --> 00:44:14.257
but since you say I helped…

00:44:25.101 --> 00:44:27.019
Two green onions…

00:44:29.397 --> 00:44:31.607
Three green onions…

00:44:33.484 --> 00:44:35.235
Isn't that for your hangover?

00:44:35.236 --> 00:44:37.696
Why are you making art
instead of eating it?

00:44:37.697 --> 00:44:41.450
I may be friendly with everyone,
but not green onions…

00:44:42.535 --> 00:44:44.829
What? Hang on.

00:44:45.746 --> 00:44:46.747
Mmm.

00:44:47.957 --> 00:44:50.208
He picked out the green onions for me.

00:44:50.209 --> 00:44:52.378
How did he know I don't eat green onions?

00:44:53.004 --> 00:44:55.923
Green onions… What does that mean?

00:44:56.799 --> 00:44:58.216
Did he flirt with green onions?

00:44:58.217 --> 00:44:59.926
I'm heading out now.

00:44:59.927 --> 00:45:01.219
Right, the tonics.

00:45:01.220 --> 00:45:05.390
I should take a tonic
that Mr. Yeon gave me.

00:45:05.391 --> 00:45:06.766
- Huh?
- Oh.

00:45:06.767 --> 00:45:10.186
I should take the vitamins
that Mr. Yeon got me.

00:45:10.187 --> 00:45:12.063
- What?
- He seemed a bit reserved,

00:45:12.064 --> 00:45:13.565
but he takes care of our whole family.

00:45:13.566 --> 00:45:15.442
He's so thoughtful.

00:45:15.443 --> 00:45:17.819
- I'll get going now.
- See you.

00:45:17.820 --> 00:45:19.196
Okay.

00:45:20.406 --> 00:45:21.407
Grandma.

00:45:22.199 --> 00:45:26.828
Did Mr. Yeon always
take care of everyone like this?

00:45:26.829 --> 00:45:28.663
What's the point of having you three?

00:45:28.664 --> 00:45:30.666
Mr. Yeon's the only one
who takes care of me.

00:45:33.127 --> 00:45:34.587
Geez.

00:45:35.379 --> 00:45:37.548
I was overreacting for no reason.

00:45:40.801 --> 00:45:41.885
Gosh, that's hot.

00:45:41.886 --> 00:45:44.804
- Great work.
- Great work, everyone.

00:45:44.805 --> 00:45:46.264
- Thank you.
- Great work.

00:45:46.265 --> 00:45:47.808
Thank you for everything.

00:45:49.143 --> 00:45:50.769
I'll see you in Seoul.

00:45:50.770 --> 00:45:52.438
Okay. I'll see you in 10 days.

00:45:52.980 --> 00:45:54.856
Oh. That's a day for pizza.

00:45:54.857 --> 00:45:56.776
How about pizza that day?

00:45:58.277 --> 00:46:00.362
- Is it a full moon?
- Mmm.

00:46:00.363 --> 00:46:01.863
Sure, pizza sounds good.

00:46:01.864 --> 00:46:03.783
And here.

00:46:04.909 --> 00:46:06.701
For the hangover stuff you gave me.

00:46:06.702 --> 00:46:08.287
HANG IN THERE!

00:46:08.746 --> 00:46:10.748
I also have…

00:46:11.999 --> 00:46:13.000
this.

00:46:13.709 --> 00:46:14.710
Hmm?

00:46:15.336 --> 00:46:16.337
Homework.

00:46:17.171 --> 00:46:18.254
A film camera?

00:46:18.255 --> 00:46:19.798
What kind of homework?

00:46:19.799 --> 00:46:21.509
Well…

00:46:22.635 --> 00:46:24.719
Ms. Song, hurry.

00:46:24.720 --> 00:46:25.805
Come on.

00:46:29.058 --> 00:46:30.559
Hurry!

00:46:32.728 --> 00:46:34.897
It would be a huge waste not to see that.

00:46:37.942 --> 00:46:40.944
Wow, it's beautiful.

00:46:40.945 --> 00:46:43.030
It's called an iridescent cloud.

00:46:43.989 --> 00:46:45.198
An iridescent cloud?

00:46:45.199 --> 00:46:47.283
We also call them
mother-of-pearl clouds.

00:46:47.284 --> 00:46:50.578
Because of the diffraction of sunlight,
the cloud particles…

00:46:50.579 --> 00:46:52.206
Forget it.

00:46:52.790 --> 00:46:54.374
It's a good omen.

00:46:54.375 --> 00:46:57.044
They say you have good luck
if you see an iridescent cloud.

00:46:58.129 --> 00:46:59.547
That's childish.

00:47:00.840 --> 00:47:02.341
Do people say it's lucky?

00:47:05.469 --> 00:47:07.346
Wait, it's blurry.

00:47:10.641 --> 00:47:15.145
You should look for iridescent clouds
in the sky, too,

00:47:15.146 --> 00:47:16.814
instead of just vapor trails.

00:47:19.692 --> 00:47:24.447
Vapor trails are just traces
of something that already passed by.

00:47:25.239 --> 00:47:28.908
But iridescent clouds
make you excited for the future.

00:47:29.994 --> 00:47:31.245
The past…

00:47:32.997 --> 00:47:36.625
may not be as beautiful as you remember.

00:47:37.168 --> 00:47:39.879
They get blurred,
overwritten, and distorted.

00:47:41.046 --> 00:47:44.550
Or they may have been romanticized
because some things…

00:47:45.551 --> 00:47:46.844
were hidden.

00:47:48.971 --> 00:47:50.972
Why are you suddenly saying that?

00:47:50.973 --> 00:47:51.974
I was just…

00:47:52.975 --> 00:47:56.144
worried that you'd miss
an iridescent cloud

00:47:56.145 --> 00:47:57.438
while staring at a vapor trail.

00:47:58.898 --> 00:48:01.983
I have a habit of feeling upset
if I miss something exciting

00:48:01.984 --> 00:48:04.487
while thinking about the past.

00:48:06.489 --> 00:48:08.281
All right, everybody. Come here!

00:48:08.282 --> 00:48:10.366
- Ending a trip…
- With a group photo…

00:48:10.367 --> 00:48:12.952
...is a must!

00:48:12.953 --> 00:48:14.204
Let's go.

00:48:20.794 --> 00:48:22.921
All right. Here goes.

00:48:22.922 --> 00:48:24.214
Hurry.

00:48:24.215 --> 00:48:26.424
Okay, everyone. What's one plus one?

00:48:26.425 --> 00:48:29.303
- Two!
- Two!

00:48:51.408 --> 00:48:53.076
But what sort of homework is this?

00:48:53.077 --> 00:48:54.702
Take one photo each day

00:48:54.703 --> 00:48:56.746
and show them to me
when I return to Seoul.

00:48:56.747 --> 00:48:58.873
Isn't it crazy, though?

00:48:58.874 --> 00:49:01.584
How did they know I'm leaving in 10 days

00:49:01.585 --> 00:49:04.212
and sell a 10-shot camera?

00:49:04.213 --> 00:49:06.256
What should I take photos of?

00:49:06.257 --> 00:49:09.259
Something fun, delicious, or pretty.

00:49:09.260 --> 00:49:12.930
Just anything
that made you feel good that day.

00:49:25.442 --> 00:49:27.194
Hang in there!

00:49:43.127 --> 00:49:46.045
- I'd like some coffee.
- It's on me, so help yourselves!

00:49:46.046 --> 00:49:48.339
- This is so good!
- I got us some coffee.

00:49:48.340 --> 00:49:49.591
What's with the coffee?

00:49:49.592 --> 00:49:52.844
I heard Je Raemee was bringing
Gyeongju bread today.

00:49:52.845 --> 00:49:54.679
I thought it would go well with coffee.

00:49:54.680 --> 00:49:55.806
Can I have one?

00:49:56.890 --> 00:49:58.308
Wasn't Gyeongju amazing?

00:49:58.309 --> 00:50:02.771
There were so many things to see and eat,
and the beach was so beautiful…

00:50:04.356 --> 00:50:05.732
What is it?

00:50:05.733 --> 00:50:09.485
We've never seen you talk for so long
about something other than work.

00:50:09.486 --> 00:50:11.488
It's the first time since I joined.

00:50:14.867 --> 00:50:16.744
Let's start working, then.

00:50:21.874 --> 00:50:23.709
She's suddenly
acting so friendly.

00:50:24.501 --> 00:50:28.129
Well, she's not tinting her windows
or brooding like before.

00:50:28.130 --> 00:50:32.050
I guess she's a tiny bit… better
than before.

00:50:34.345 --> 00:50:36.680
Hello.

00:50:43.854 --> 00:50:46.565
Wow. You and sweet and sour candy?

00:50:47.191 --> 00:50:48.650
That really doesn't suit you.

00:50:48.651 --> 00:50:51.612
Ah. I guess you're giving it to someone.

00:50:52.446 --> 00:50:53.447
Pardon?

00:50:54.031 --> 00:50:55.991
Would you like one?

00:50:56.575 --> 00:50:57.743
Sure.

00:50:58.243 --> 00:51:00.079
I'll try one, then.

00:51:01.455 --> 00:51:02.539
Thank you.

00:51:18.347 --> 00:51:19.430
Hello.

00:51:19.431 --> 00:51:22.225
I'm Yeon Taeseok
from Seoul Commercial High School.

00:51:22.226 --> 00:51:25.186
Mr. Yeon Taeseok.

00:51:25.187 --> 00:51:27.272
Even your name sounds proper.

00:51:28.232 --> 00:51:30.317
But you said hello to the wrong person.

00:51:30.818 --> 00:51:33.277
Oh… Sorry.

00:51:33.278 --> 00:51:35.906
No need to apologize.

00:51:36.407 --> 00:51:39.785
Wow. You're sweating a lot.

00:51:40.911 --> 00:51:42.579
Ah.

00:51:44.123 --> 00:51:45.623
Would you like one?

00:51:46.792 --> 00:51:49.293
The sour taste will snap you awake,

00:51:49.294 --> 00:51:51.255
and the sweet taste will help you relax.

00:51:52.131 --> 00:51:54.966
Eat that to relax your nerves.

00:51:54.967 --> 00:51:56.175
Thank you.

00:51:56.176 --> 00:51:57.177
And…

00:51:57.803 --> 00:51:59.722
There's a piece of tissue here.

00:52:00.431 --> 00:52:03.307
Then good luck.

00:52:03.308 --> 00:52:05.394
- You can do it.
- Right.

00:52:08.313 --> 00:52:11.191
I tried to get some pocket money
from Grandma but got a noogie.

00:52:20.033 --> 00:52:23.286
Mr. Yeon Taeseok,
Ms. Kim will see you now.

00:52:23.287 --> 00:52:24.288
Okay.

00:52:33.380 --> 00:52:34.465
Thank you.

00:52:43.891 --> 00:52:44.933
I'll be right back.

00:52:45.434 --> 00:52:46.643
Hadam!

00:52:51.190 --> 00:52:53.233
Are you going to your math academy?

00:52:53.901 --> 00:52:55.818
What is it?

00:52:55.819 --> 00:52:57.696
You look worried about something.

00:52:59.072 --> 00:53:01.992
What is it?
Tell your boyfriend everything.

00:53:03.786 --> 00:53:05.078
Yougyum.

00:53:07.331 --> 00:53:10.541
Did you go to a jewelry shop
a few days ago…

00:53:10.542 --> 00:53:12.084
Hey, Yougyum!

00:53:12.085 --> 00:53:15.339
Enough with the PDA and get back here.
We have to practice.

00:53:16.006 --> 00:53:18.591
Go on. We'll talk later.

00:53:18.592 --> 00:53:20.802
I'll call you later.

00:53:25.390 --> 00:53:28.684
If anything is bothering you, tell me.
I'll take care of everything…

00:53:28.685 --> 00:53:31.395
I mean, everything besides studying.

00:53:31.396 --> 00:53:33.941
All right.

00:53:35.025 --> 00:53:37.027
Hang in there!

00:53:38.862 --> 00:53:41.364
Park Yeseul…

00:53:41.365 --> 00:53:44.159
Why did she have to bring up
Han Sora?

00:53:47.412 --> 00:53:48.997
CHA YOUGYUM

00:53:51.166 --> 00:53:53.543
SORA

00:53:55.587 --> 00:53:56.630
Yes, Ms. Kim.

00:53:58.257 --> 00:53:59.633
The revised sketch?

00:54:00.300 --> 00:54:02.302
No. I'll hand it in by today.

00:54:03.762 --> 00:54:04.847
Okay.

00:54:08.308 --> 00:54:11.644
I really need an idea. Please…

00:54:18.068 --> 00:54:20.195
I'm sending you a photo
since you said yours was blurry.

00:54:28.704 --> 00:54:30.831
Ms. Song, the material check…

00:54:31.498 --> 00:54:34.501
What happened to your hair?

00:54:35.252 --> 00:54:38.504
Whoa. What's that? The colors are amazing.

00:54:38.505 --> 00:54:42.383
I saw it for the first time in Gyeongju.
It's called an iridescent cloud.

00:54:42.384 --> 00:54:43.718
It's a cloud?

00:54:43.719 --> 00:54:45.386
Wow. It looks like a rainbow.

00:54:45.387 --> 00:54:47.347
They call it a rainbow cloud, too.

00:54:47.973 --> 00:54:49.766
It's also called a mother-of-pearl cloud…

00:54:51.184 --> 00:54:52.893
because of the color…

00:54:58.025 --> 00:55:01.695
- Oh. Can you get my rolling cart?
- What?

00:55:02.738 --> 00:55:03.780
Right.

00:55:33.644 --> 00:55:35.395
Here's the revised outfit design.

00:55:35.979 --> 00:55:37.606
Sorry, I'm late.

00:55:45.864 --> 00:55:47.990
It wasn't just a simple revision.

00:55:47.991 --> 00:55:52.203
The color was important,
so I made a colored illustration.

00:55:52.204 --> 00:55:54.872
That's a color palette
I haven't seen before.

00:55:54.873 --> 00:55:59.251
I applied mother-of-pearl colors
on the basic silhouette.

00:55:59.252 --> 00:56:02.004
Mother-of-pearl…

00:56:02.005 --> 00:56:04.006
- As in shiny seashells?
- Yes.

00:56:04.007 --> 00:56:08.803
I thought it could be a great material
to highlight a Korean aesthetic.

00:56:08.804 --> 00:56:12.890
For now, I just expressed
the general vibe with gloss pens,

00:56:12.891 --> 00:56:15.685
but if we can capture
the texture of mother-of-pearl

00:56:15.686 --> 00:56:18.145
so it has a mysterious glow
whenever she moves,

00:56:18.146 --> 00:56:21.107
I think that would add some fun
to the animation as well.

00:56:21.108 --> 00:56:22.441
Well…

00:56:22.442 --> 00:56:23.610
Not bad.

00:56:24.152 --> 00:56:26.113
Mother-of-pearl is normally used
for decorations.

00:56:26.697 --> 00:56:28.739
How did you come up with the idea
of using its colors?

00:56:28.740 --> 00:56:29.741
Oh…

00:56:30.617 --> 00:56:33.744
This is an iridescent cloud
I saw in Gyeongju.

00:56:33.745 --> 00:56:36.163
This photo became a great inspiration.

00:56:36.164 --> 00:56:38.791
I heard it's also called
a mother-of-pearl cloud

00:56:38.792 --> 00:56:39.917
because of its colors.

00:56:41.253 --> 00:56:42.503
Mmm.

00:56:42.504 --> 00:56:47.592
It will go well with Raemee's idea
of emphasizing the collar and front panel.

00:56:50.137 --> 00:56:51.430
So that trip wasn't for nothing.

00:56:53.098 --> 00:56:54.307
You can go.

00:56:55.517 --> 00:56:56.685
Okay.

00:57:04.901 --> 00:57:06.486
She won't need me anymore.

00:57:09.322 --> 00:57:10.574
Hmm?

00:57:11.533 --> 00:57:13.118
My sketch finally got accepted.

00:57:18.999 --> 00:57:21.083
Huh? Wait.

00:57:21.084 --> 00:57:23.294
Was this inspired
by that iridescent cloud?

00:57:23.295 --> 00:57:26.465
That's right. You said it's also
called a mother-of-pearl cloud.

00:57:27.132 --> 00:57:29.509
It's all thanks to you.
I'll treat you to 10 pizzas.

00:57:33.096 --> 00:57:34.681
Let's see…

00:57:46.818 --> 00:57:48.820
Mmm…

00:57:50.280 --> 00:57:52.949
They say you have good luck
if you see an iridescent cloud.

00:57:53.658 --> 00:57:55.826
He was right.

00:57:55.827 --> 00:57:58.955
It worked out
thanks to him.

00:58:00.582 --> 00:58:01.958
The cloud you saw in Gyeongju?

00:58:02.876 --> 00:58:06.921
Why do I feel like
I know who you saw it with?

00:58:06.922 --> 00:58:08.005
What?

00:58:08.006 --> 00:58:12.927
The Haran before wasn't my style,
so she was about 0.5 points,

00:58:12.928 --> 00:58:15.680
but the new Song Haran
after our Gyeongju trip… Tsk.

00:58:16.181 --> 00:58:17.557
Right, I'll give you three points.

00:58:18.183 --> 00:58:19.851
Fine. I'll give you 3.5.

00:58:20.769 --> 00:58:22.770
- Excuse me?
- Don't get too excited.

00:58:22.771 --> 00:58:24.105
My points…

00:58:24.898 --> 00:58:26.899
are out of 10.

00:58:33.949 --> 00:58:35.325
All right.

00:58:43.708 --> 00:58:46.795
Didn't I tell you to stop coming?

00:58:53.260 --> 00:58:54.552
It's grated yam.

00:58:54.553 --> 00:58:56.638
I did some research,
and they said it helps.

00:58:57.138 --> 00:58:59.765
I'm already taking good care of myself.

00:58:59.766 --> 00:59:02.351
Just focus on baseball.

00:59:02.352 --> 00:59:05.105
I'm practicing really hard too, you know.

00:59:06.731 --> 00:59:09.775
But what about
that examination you mentioned last time?

00:59:09.776 --> 00:59:10.777
It's next week.

00:59:11.653 --> 00:59:14.238
Are you getting along well with Hadam?

00:59:14.239 --> 00:59:16.574
Why aren't you talking
about marriage anymore?

00:59:16.575 --> 00:59:20.495
I decided to support her quietly
until the CSAT so I wouldn't distract her.

00:59:21.079 --> 00:59:23.289
Have you been wearing
that necklace I gave you?

00:59:23.290 --> 00:59:25.374
If it's not the right length, I can…

00:59:25.375 --> 00:59:26.668
GUARDIAN

00:59:27.502 --> 00:59:29.879
You're just a student.
Where did you get the money?

00:59:29.880 --> 00:59:32.548
I'm a future Major Leaguer, you know.

00:59:32.549 --> 00:59:35.926
Gosh. I should get
an autograph in advance.

00:59:38.597 --> 00:59:42.058
Huh? Did you hit your leg somewhere?

00:59:42.642 --> 00:59:45.061
It's fine. I just fell.

00:59:45.812 --> 00:59:47.731
My legs suddenly wouldn't listen.

00:59:52.193 --> 00:59:55.906
You have to make sure
Hadam doesn't find out until the CSAT.

00:59:57.991 --> 01:00:01.620
Okay. I'll take good care of her.

01:00:13.882 --> 01:00:16.300
- Hello?
- Are you free next next Friday at 7 p.m.?

01:00:16.301 --> 01:00:18.178
Next next Friday?

01:00:19.304 --> 01:00:21.597
- Well, yes…
- Okay.

01:00:21.598 --> 01:00:25.392
Then let's have dinner at Samcheong-dong.

01:00:25.393 --> 01:00:26.603
Samcheong-dong?

01:00:27.854 --> 01:00:30.773
It's a one-table restaurant
I booked before coming to Korea.

01:00:30.774 --> 01:00:32.316
Maybe it's thanks to that cloud.

01:00:32.317 --> 01:00:33.859
There was a long waitlist,

01:00:33.860 --> 01:00:36.779
but I just got a call
that someone canceled for that day.

01:00:36.780 --> 01:00:38.656
- Mmm.
- I'll send you the link.

01:00:38.657 --> 01:00:40.158
I haven't seen this place before.

01:00:40.825 --> 01:00:42.201
I confirmed the reservation.

01:00:42.202 --> 01:00:44.495
Ah. Mark that on your schedule.

01:00:44.496 --> 01:00:46.580
You'd better not forget or show up late.

01:00:50.210 --> 01:00:52.170
I got distracted.

01:01:12.691 --> 01:01:14.734
Good morning. Did you sleep well?

01:01:15.276 --> 01:01:18.279
Our team did a sunrise shoot,
so everyone's knocked out now.

01:01:19.280 --> 01:01:20.573
Hey, a flower bloomed.

01:01:21.533 --> 01:01:24.577
But why aren't you sleeping?
Aren't you tired?

01:01:25.328 --> 01:01:27.038
I have to enjoy every moment.

01:01:27.622 --> 01:01:30.208
Ah. There's a beautiful half-moon.

01:01:31.042 --> 01:01:32.669
Can you see it clearly in Seoul?

01:01:35.922 --> 01:01:37.549
Yes, I can.

01:01:41.052 --> 01:01:43.471
So today's dinner is omurice.

01:01:51.813 --> 01:01:52.814
Donggu?

01:01:53.648 --> 01:01:56.401
- Hello.
- Hi.

01:02:02.824 --> 01:02:06.618
What did you draw that character
on Donggu's uniform with?

01:02:06.619 --> 01:02:08.662
A fabric marker?

01:02:08.663 --> 01:02:09.914
That's right.

01:02:15.045 --> 01:02:17.796
Right. Mr. Park's checkup is on Wednesday.

01:02:17.797 --> 01:02:19.591
Can you check up on him?

01:02:20.592 --> 01:02:22.009
Mr. Park.

01:02:22.010 --> 01:02:23.635
Hey, you're here.

01:02:23.636 --> 01:02:24.762
Genius.

01:02:28.183 --> 01:02:30.434
You didn't forget your checkup, right?

01:02:30.435 --> 01:02:34.104
There's someone
calling me every day to remind me,

01:02:34.105 --> 01:02:36.356
so I remember it
more clearly than my own birthday.

01:02:37.942 --> 01:02:40.444
But have you started a new hobby?

01:02:40.445 --> 01:02:42.113
You've been taking a lot of photos.

01:02:42.697 --> 01:02:45.491
Ah. Someone gave me homework,

01:02:45.492 --> 01:02:47.826
telling me to take photos
of what makes me happy.

01:02:47.827 --> 01:02:50.871
Mmm. So what did you take photos of?

01:02:50.872 --> 01:02:52.539
Nothing special.

01:02:52.540 --> 01:02:54.249
Just people around me,

01:02:54.250 --> 01:02:57.544
the moon, delicious food,

01:02:57.545 --> 01:02:59.213
that flower… Things like that.

01:02:59.214 --> 01:03:00.672
Oh.

01:03:00.673 --> 01:03:03.801
I'm so curious how they'll look.

01:03:03.802 --> 01:03:07.347
They say happiness is always there,
but you just miss it,

01:03:07.972 --> 01:03:11.475
so it belongs to the person
who discovers it.

01:03:11.476 --> 01:03:12.602
I guess it's true.

01:03:13.436 --> 01:03:15.647
I went on a walk with Genius earlier,

01:03:16.231 --> 01:03:18.357
and the sky was so beautiful.

01:03:18.358 --> 01:03:20.235
But no one even looked up.

01:03:20.985 --> 01:03:24.947
They were all walking around,
staring at their phones.

01:03:40.964 --> 01:03:42.631
I have a feeling

01:03:42.632 --> 01:03:45.592
that the person who gave you that camera…

01:03:46.678 --> 01:03:49.471
...is someone who knows
how to look up at the sky

01:03:49.472 --> 01:03:51.141
on days like this.

01:03:52.851 --> 01:03:55.728
I guess that's why
they gave you that homework.

01:03:56.437 --> 01:04:01.692
So you can discover nice things every day,
no matter how trivial they are.

01:04:01.693 --> 01:04:05.654
They probably wanted you
to smile at least once while doing so.

01:04:05.655 --> 01:04:07.949
Isn't that right?

01:04:14.706 --> 01:04:16.708
Mr. Park, I think I get it now.

01:04:17.167 --> 01:04:18.250
What?

01:04:18.251 --> 01:04:22.045
I was surprised at how different I was
these days, but I didn't know why.

01:04:22.046 --> 01:04:25.717
I guess that's because
it's been such a long time since I saw it.

01:04:26.634 --> 01:04:28.511
Saw what?

01:04:29.971 --> 01:04:31.055
Myself.

01:04:33.183 --> 01:04:35.894
My past self.

01:04:40.815 --> 01:04:43.859
I used to be able to find happiness
in the smallest things.

01:04:45.111 --> 01:04:47.779
It's been a while since I saw
that side of me.

01:04:50.992 --> 01:04:53.870
I was able to see it again
thanks to someone.

01:04:54.829 --> 01:04:56.539
I guess that's why I was surprised.

01:05:00.793 --> 01:05:02.879
Mmm.

01:05:04.422 --> 01:05:05.590
Oh, my.

01:05:06.549 --> 01:05:09.509
The moon is beautiful.

01:05:11.262 --> 01:05:13.139
I hope I can see a full moon soon.

01:05:34.118 --> 01:05:35.912
Where can I find a photo studio?

01:05:41.376 --> 01:05:44.002
Remember, we're stopping
at the rest area halfway, okay?

01:05:44.003 --> 01:05:45.212
- Okay.
- See you later, bro!

01:05:45.213 --> 01:05:47.130
- Okay. See you guys.
- Drive safely. See you.

01:05:47.131 --> 01:05:48.215
Sorry, Ben.

01:05:48.216 --> 01:05:49.341
Take a different car.

01:05:49.342 --> 01:05:51.426
I'm going straight to Seoul.

01:05:51.427 --> 01:05:53.053
But it's at least four hours.

01:05:53.054 --> 01:05:55.472
- Bye.
- Hey, don't strain yourself.

01:05:55.473 --> 01:05:56.974
I'll drive.

01:05:56.975 --> 01:05:58.892
Huh? I said I'll drive.

01:05:58.893 --> 01:06:01.103
It's fine. I'll see you in Seoul.

01:06:01.104 --> 01:06:03.021
- Hey!
- I'm fine, Ben.

01:06:03.022 --> 01:06:05.984
Seonu Chan! Drive slowly, okay?

01:06:08.945 --> 01:06:10.697
He really
shouldn't be driving.

01:06:18.413 --> 01:06:20.206
I'll arrive around 6:30 p.m.

01:06:21.165 --> 01:06:22.499
Find a nice pizza place for us.

01:06:22.500 --> 01:06:23.584
See you later.

01:06:37.056 --> 01:06:39.100
ETA
1 HOUR

01:06:40.435 --> 01:06:41.644
One hour.

01:07:01.372 --> 01:07:02.790
Oh? Has he arrived early?

01:07:07.128 --> 01:07:09.422
- Yes, Ms. Kim.
- Come to my office.

01:07:10.423 --> 01:07:11.841
MS. KIM

01:07:12.925 --> 01:07:14.135
Right now?

01:07:20.141 --> 01:07:21.558
Me?

01:07:21.559 --> 01:07:23.602
Yes, you. Who else?

01:07:23.603 --> 01:07:25.937
Why would you make me handle the business?

01:07:25.938 --> 01:07:29.107
I'm retiring later than planned,
and you held on longer than I thought.

01:07:29.108 --> 01:07:30.151
It's time you took over.

01:07:31.277 --> 01:07:32.986
I didn't get to go at 60 as I planned,

01:07:32.987 --> 01:07:35.239
but I'm going to retire soon
and go to France.

01:07:35.823 --> 01:07:36.824
So start preparing.

01:07:37.533 --> 01:07:39.993
No, I can't do this.

01:07:39.994 --> 01:07:43.580
I'm already overwhelmed with doing design,
and I'm not qualified…

01:07:43.581 --> 01:07:45.166
You'll develop your abilities.

01:07:45.792 --> 01:07:47.168
And that was an order, not an offer.

01:07:47.752 --> 01:07:49.211
I'm not making excuses, I--

01:07:49.212 --> 01:07:50.670
You don't have a choice.

01:07:50.671 --> 01:07:53.215
If you really can't do it, then quit.

01:07:53.216 --> 01:07:55.967
I raise people for their abilities,
not with sentiment.

01:07:55.968 --> 01:07:57.011
I'll give you…

01:07:58.554 --> 01:07:59.888
a week for that report.

01:08:07.313 --> 01:08:08.815
This is so sudden…

01:08:12.735 --> 01:08:14.821
MISSED CALL
ANIMATOR SEONU CHAN

01:08:16.572 --> 01:08:19.366
The number you have dialed
is unavailable. Please leave--

01:08:19.367 --> 01:08:20.993
Why is it off?

01:08:24.831 --> 01:08:26.916
Call me when you get my message.

01:08:29.252 --> 01:08:32.171
I couldn't react properly…

01:08:32.755 --> 01:08:34.298
Was he driving here?

01:08:36.717 --> 01:08:39.554
- Mr. Park, did you hear from Mr. Seonu?
- Oh?

01:08:40.138 --> 01:08:42.223
I guess you haven't heard yet.

01:08:43.766 --> 01:08:44.976
I got a call.

01:08:46.602 --> 01:08:47.854
What call?

01:08:49.480 --> 01:08:51.482
He suddenly had to return to America.

01:08:52.150 --> 01:08:54.193
He had to head straight to the airport,

01:08:54.735 --> 01:08:57.488
so he asked me to send
his passport through express delivery.

01:08:58.906 --> 01:09:00.949
I don't know what's going on, either.

01:09:00.950 --> 01:09:04.995
He said he'd call me again soon,
but he hasn't called.

01:09:10.793 --> 01:09:11.919
What…

01:09:13.004 --> 01:09:15.339
- I…
- He would have left already.

01:09:16.466 --> 01:09:20.177
He said he'd take
the earliest flight to the US.

01:09:20.178 --> 01:09:22.263
He must be gone already.

01:09:36.527 --> 01:09:38.988
MISSED CALL
ANIMATOR SEONU CHAN

01:09:46.245 --> 01:09:48.121
YOUR PHOTOS ARE READY FOR PICKUP

01:09:48.122 --> 01:09:49.207
HOBAK PHOTO STUDIO

01:10:18.736 --> 01:10:21.322
What? He said there were 10 shots.

01:10:22.865 --> 01:10:24.033
He was lying.

01:10:53.396 --> 01:10:54.856
Keep enjoying your life

01:10:55.273 --> 01:10:58.109
even when… I'm not here later.

01:11:19.922 --> 01:11:21.841
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

01:11:45.948 --> 01:11:47.616
They are all gone?

01:11:47.617 --> 01:11:50.785
What kind of trial ends like this?

01:11:50.786 --> 01:11:53.580
- Ms. Kim!
- Why did you go to the hospital?

01:11:53.581 --> 01:11:55.206
Are you sick?

01:11:55.207 --> 01:11:56.708
I just want to walk for a bit.

01:11:56.709 --> 01:11:59.419
Chan was such a nice guy.

01:11:59.420 --> 01:12:02.172
When we first met,

01:12:02.173 --> 01:12:04.883
he said I looked like
someone trapped in winter.

01:12:04.884 --> 01:12:07.510
You're not worried about Haran?

01:12:07.511 --> 01:12:09.179
Do you regret it?

01:12:09.180 --> 01:12:12.433
Do you regret getting close to Seonu Chan?

01:12:13.017 --> 01:12:14.894
Yes, I do.

01:12:27.323 --> 01:12:28.406
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

01:12:28.407 --> 01:12:29.408
Translated by Juyoung Park